mission of producing young men and women who are global citizens  Cadets are more likely to study abroad if they feel that their professors  academic advisers  and study abroad advisers are supportive   We want to make it easy for you to guide your cadets academically through the process and support them through letters of recommendation  Propose a Faculty Led Program Help your cadets discover a world beyond the VMI classroom   Make them the great global citizens they can be while enhancing their job opportunities   General Order 73 outlines the process for taking cadets abroad   The first step is to complete the proposal form by clicking here and then scheduling a meeting with the Office of International Programs  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 